Earl GARDNER, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES, Appellee. No. 8139. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 8, 1936. Daniel E. Rienhardt and Cullen A. Little,, both of Globe, Ariz., for appellant. Frank E. Flynn, U. S. Atty., of Phoenix, Ariz.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of motion of counsel for appellee, consented to by counsel for appellant, and after examination of the bill of exceptions herein, ordered motion granted; appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
